        h3 Prerequisites
        p (EECS 161 or CS 161)

        h3 Course Description
        p Basic data structures. Computer programming techniques and application of software engineering principles. Introduction to analysis of programs.

        h3 Course Content:
        ul.none
            li File I/O
            li Object-oriented programming principles
            li Program design, debugging and testing
            li Algorithm analysis
            li Recursion
            li Sorting and searching
            li Linear data structures
            li Debugging and testing


        h3 Course Objectives
        ol 
            li Design and implement programs that require
            ol(type="a")
                li multiple classes and structures
                li hierarchies of classes that uses inheritance and polymorphism
                li an understanding of abstraction, modularity and separation of concerns

            li 	Construct and use basic linear structures (arrays, stacks, queues, and various linked lists) in programs, and be able to describe instances appropriate for their use.
            li 	Classify moderately complicated algorithms in these complexity classes: O(1), O(log n), O(n), O(n log n), and O(n2).
            li 	Develop test-data sets and testing plans for programming projects. 
            li 	Produce recursive algorithms, and choose appropriately between iterative and recursive algorithms. 



        p A detailed description and time-line of the topics covered in this course can be on the <a href="../calendar/calendar.html"/>calendar page</a>. This calendar is strictly a guide for the course. It is tentative and subject to change. You can find the topics covered in the daily lectures in slides posted on the calendar page, and the assignments with their corresponding actual due dates are located on the <a href="../assignments/assignments.html"> assignments page</a>.

