            li When a class is missed, it is the STUDENT'S responsibility to obtain any notes, assignments, etc. from classmates.
            li Lab attendance is required. <b>YOU WILL RECEIVE A ZERO FOR ANY UNEXCUSED MISSED LABS.</b> A zero lab grade cannot change!!!
            li Excused absences must be approved by your <b>lecture, lab, or recitation instructor.</b> <b>BE PROACTIVE!!!</b>
            ul.none
                li For labs, send an email to cs162-ta@engr.orst.edu with <b>CS 162 Lab Absence in the subject.</b>
                li For recitations, send an email to cs162-recitation@engr.orst.edu with <b>CS 162 Recitation Absence in the subject.</b>
                li For class absences, send an email to parhammj@engr.orst.edu with <b>CS 162 Course Absence in the subject.</b>
            li Students are still responsible for lab work missed even when their absence was excused.
            li Students can ONLY make-up in-class exercises with an approved absence. <b>BE PROACTIVE!!!</b>
            li Please, be on time for lecture AND turn off your cell phone ringer because it can be disruptive to other students, as well as the instructor.
            li <b>Laptops and other electronics are NOT allowed during lecture, unless approved by the instructor.</b> There is a study that shows you lower yours and your peer's grade by using a laptop in the classroom: <a href="http://www.cbc.ca/news/technology/laptop-use-lowers-student-grades-experiment-shows-1.1401860">Laptop Study</a>. In addition, there are studies that show traditional note taking by hand aids in a student's learning: <a href="http://chronicle.com/blogs/linguafranca/2014/08/25/why-im-asking-you-not-to-use-laptops/?cid=cr&amp;utm_source=cr&amp;utm_medium=en"> Another Study</a>. Our course requires those who have authorization by the instructor to sit in a particular section of the classroom to prevent distracting others.
