        h3 Grade Evaluation Scores for labs, recitations, assignments, and exams will be posted on Canvas as they are graded.
        h4 Labs - 10%
        ul.none
            li There are 10 total labs in this course, i.e. one to be completed each lecture week.
            li You MUST attend the lab in which you are registered, unless receiving permission PRIOR to missing the lab!!! (Read Attendance policy!)
            li Some parts of the lab will be group work while others will be individual work.  You can submit one copy for any portion of the lab that is group work.
            li Labs are graded on a 10-point scale and primarily based on participation and effort, rather than correctness.
            li You are <b>required to bring a laptop to the lab</b>.
            li These labs are supposed to enhance the lectures using hands-on learning.
            li Labs are designed to be finished in 70-90 minutes and graded during lab time by your lab instructor.
            li If you attended a lab and did not finish, you can finish <b>up to 3 points of the lab</b> at home and bring it with you to the next week's lab for a grade.  You must show your update from the previous lab within the first 15 minutes of the current lab to redeem points on the prior lab, otherwise the work is not accepted.
            li If you have a problem with a lab grade, <b>you must contact your lab instructor through EMAIL within ONE WEEK</b> of receiving your grade.  After one week, you will not be able to dispute your grade.

        h4   Recitation Exercises - 20%
        ul.none
            li The recitations consist of 5 designs, 10 peer-to-peer design critiques, and 10 quizzes.
            li Attendance is required for recitations, and <b>YOU WILL RECEIVE A ZERO</b> for the quiz portion of ANY UNEXCUSED MISSED RECITATION!!! 
            li You MUST attend the recitation in which you are registered, unless receiving permission PRIOR to missing the recitation!!! (Read Attendance policy!)
            li The recitations are used to check and supplement student understanding, and the grades will be based on designs (40%), quizzes (40%), and critiques (20%).

        h4   Assignments - 30%
        ul.none
            li There are 5 total assignments to be completed over the course of this class.
            li DO NOT expect answers to emails about assignments after 5pm on the day it is due!!!
            li All assignments include writing a computer program, which MUST compile and execute on ENGR. 
            li Programming assignments that do not compile will receive a grade of <b>zero on the implementation portion of the assignment without any exceptions. 
            li Assignments are to be turned in before Midnight (<strong>by 11:59pm) on Sunday night, otherwise the assignment is late.
            li You will turn in your assignments through hand-in on the 
                a(href="https://secure.engr.oregonstate.edu:8000/teach.php?type=want_auth") TEACH website.  
            li Programs are evaluated on how well they solve the assigned problem (adherence to program specification), proper formatting/use of comments, and creativity:) 
            li <b>Only one late assignment is allowed during the term</b>. This assignment will be accepted without penalty up to 3 days from the original due date. Outside of 3 days, the assignment will not be accepted!!!  You turn in your assignment to TEACH, just as you would normally.
            li Programming assignments in this course are graded by demoing your work for 10 minutes with a TA. You are required to <b>meet with a TA</b> within two weeks of the due date to demo. You can schedule a demo with a TA on the <a href="../index.html">home page</a> in the far right column of the bottom table labeled "Grading Hours".
        ul.none
            li <b>Demo Outside 2 Weeks:</b> Assignments that are not demo'd within the acceptable time period will be subject to a 50 point deduction.
            li <b>Demo Late Assignments:</b> Late assignments must still be demoed within the two week demo period beginning from the assignment's original due date.
            li <b>Missing a Demo:</b> If you miss your demo with a TA, you will receive a 10 point (one letter grade) deduction to that assignment for each demo missed.

            li If you have a problem with an assignment grade, <b>you must contact your TAs through EMAIL</b> within ONE WEEK of receiving your grade.  After one week, you will not be able to dispute your grade.
            li Remember to use your TAs because they are the ones who execute, read, and grade the assignments.

        h4  Exams - 30%  (15% each exam)
        ul.none
            li The are 2 total exams for this course.
            li The exams are true/false and multiple-choice, and they will be given during lecture time.
            li A student must notify the instructor BEFORE the exam to schedule a make-up.

        h4  Final Exam- 10%
        ul.none
